#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-03-04-path-resolution-in-quarkus.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We have had an unusually bumpy ride the last few weeks. Path resolution can "
"be sneakily complicated, and in trying to make things better, we "
"accidentally made them worse! We've fixed it all now, but you might notice "
"some changes. Hopefully, this post will make clear what those changes are, "
"what they mean, and what you can do to put everything back the way you want "
"it."
msgstr ""
"过去几周，我们经历了一次异常颠簸的旅程。路径解析可能是偷偷摸摸地复杂的，在试图使事情变得更好时，我们不小心使它们变得更糟了！我们现在已经全部修复了，但你可能会注意到一些变化。我们现在都已经修好了，但你可能会注意到一些变化。希望这篇文章能让你清楚这些变化是什么，它们意味着什么，以及你可以做什么来把一切恢复到你想要的样子。"

#: _posts/2021-03-04-path-resolution-in-quarkus.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**TL;DR:** As of `1.11.5.Final` and `1.12.1.Final`, leading slashes matter "
"in config. So if you use `/endpoint`, that endpoint will be served from the "
"absolute root. If you want it relative to some containing bucket, omit that "
"leading slash. For example, `quarkus.http.non-application-root-path` is now "
"`q` by default, which nests it under `quarkus.http.root-path`, matching the "
"original behavior. You can use an absolute path, e.g. `/q`, to serve non-"
"application endpoints from the absolute root (as a sibling of the http root, "
"if that is set). To remove the non-application endpoint behavior entirely, "
"set `quarkus.http.non-application-root-path` to the same value as `quarkus."
"http.root-path`. The most foolproof way to do this is using a variable: "
"`quarkus.http.non-application-root-path=${quarkus.http.root-path}`."
msgstr ""
"*提示：* 从 `1.11.5.Final` 和 `1.12.1.Final` 开始，配置中的前导斜线很重要。因此，如果使用 `/endpoint` "
"，端点将从绝对根目录提供服务。如果你想让它相对于某个包含的桶，请省略前导斜杠。例如，默认情况下 `quarkus.http.non-"
"application-root-path` 现在是 `q` ，它嵌套在 `quarkus.http.root-path` "
"下，与原始行为一致。您可以使用绝对路径，例如 `/q` ，从绝对根（作为 http "
"根的同级根，如果已设置）为非应用端点提供服务。要完全删除非应用端点行为，可将 `quarkus.http.non-application-root-"
"path` 设置为与 `quarkus.http.root-path` 相同的值。最简单的方法是使用一个变量： `quarkus.http.non-"
"application-root-path=${quarkus.http.root-path}` 。"

